cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a joint model for multi-person pose estimation. The use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The approach also involves learning a stopping criterion, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the model on the MSCOCO dataset suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of the approach for robotic applications suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
